+Feature: Methodology conformance
+
+  Scenarios in this feature verify the project follows Shipshape methodology rules. These are @conformance scenarios attesting the project's own method, not product behaviour.
+
+  @captain @conformance
+  Scenario: Watchbill shape conformance
+    When I check watchbill shape conformance
+    Then the watchbill conforms to the required schema
+
+  @captain @conformance
+  Scenario: Perturbation quiescence
+    When I scan implementation for PERTURBATION tokens
+    Then no standing PERTURBATION tokens are found
+
+  @captain @conformance
+  Scenario: Stale plank join
+    When I check every @planks annotation matches a current step definition pattern
+    Then no stale planks are found
+
+  @captain @conformance
+  Scenario: Plank form
+    When I verify every @planks token is a docblock tag on a declaration
+    Then all planks are properly formed
+
+  @captain @conformance
+  Scenario: Verification lint conformance
+    When I lint verification support with biome
+    Then no verification agreement violations are found
+
+  @captain @conformance
+  Scenario: Lint configuration
+    When I check the project lint configuration
+    Then lint is configured for the project stack
+
+  @captain @conformance
+  Scenario: Feature lint configuration
+    When I check the project feature lint configuration
+    Then feature lint is configured for Gherkin files
